se 01..29. Examples: valid_date(\'03-11-2000\') => True; valid_date(\'15-01-2012\') => False; valid_date(\'04-0-2040\') => False; valid_date(\'06-04-2020\') => True; valid_date(\'06/04/2020\') => False. Implementation guidance: import re; use re.fullmatch to enforce the format; parse month/day into integers and check ranges as above; return True/False accordingly. After writing, verify the file exists on disk at /Users/user1/CODE/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/valid_date.py and then confirm completion.",\n            "send_to": "Alex"\n        }\n    },\n    {\n        "command_name": "RoleZero.reply_to_human",\n        "args": {\n            "content": "I have created a new plan and assigned the implementation to Alex with the exact file path and constraints. He’ll write valid_date.py to /Users/user1/CODE/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline containing only the function and necessary imports, verify it’s saved to disk, and then we’ll confirm completion."\n        }\n    }\n]\n```'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': 'Command Plan.append_task executed\n\nCommand TeamLeader.publish_team_message executed\n\nCommand RoleZero.reply_to_human executed: SUCCESS, human has received your reply. Refrain from resending duplicate messages.  If you no longer need to take action, use the command ‘end’ to stop.'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': "[Message] from Mike to Alex: Alex, please implement and save the Python 3 function valid_date(date) exactly per the user's rules. Path and filename: /Users/user1/CODE/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/valid_date.py. File requirements: ONLY import(s) and the function implementation; no extra prints, tests, or comments. Rules: - Non-empty string input. - Exact format mm-dd-yyyy (two-digit month and day, four-digit year) with hyphens. - Month 01..12. - Day ranges: for 01,03,05,07,08,10,12 use 01..31; for 04,06,09,11 use 01..30; for 02 use 01..29. Examples: valid_date('03-11-2000') => True; valid_date('15-01-2012') => False; valid_date('04-0-2040') => False; valid_date('06